Fred KUBECK v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4828. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. May 8, 1933. Clarence W. Nichols and Dixson H. By-num, both of Indianapolis, Ind., and William A. McClellan, of Muneie, Ind., for appellant. George R. Jeffrey, U. S. Atty., of Indianapolis, Ind., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER, EVANS, and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, it is ordered and adjudged by this court that this appeal bo, and the same is hereby, dismissed. It is further ordered that the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
